# Aura Engine Development Workflow

## Iteration loop (every engine)

1. Implement pure TypeScript in `src/engines/<engine>.ts` (no UI changes unless requested).
2. Add tests in `src/engines/__tests__/<engine>.test.ts`.
3. Run validation in order:
   - `npm run typecheck`
   - `npm test` (or targeted `npm run test:<engine>`)
   - `npm run build`
4. Commit one engine at a time with `feat:` / `fix:` prefix.

## Safe commands (auto-run allowed)

- `npm run build`, `npm test`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run test:*`
- `npx vite-node src/engines/__tests__/*`
- `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`, `git add`, `git commit`

## Always ask before running

- `rm`, `del`, `Remove-Item`, file deletes
- `git reset --hard`, `git push --force`, `git clean -fd`
- `git push` (confirm with user unless explicitly requested)
- `npm uninstall`, dependency removals, large cross-module refactors
- System-level or out-of-repo destructive commands

## Engine conventions

- Read contracts from `@/types/aura-engine-contracts.ts`.
- Seed data: `src/data/StudentLearningProfile.json` + `src/data/blueprint.*.json`.
- Keep engines pure; React hooks live in `src/hooks/` only when needed.
- Do not redesign UI while building engines.
